akdown or in radical breaches from the ordinary, it offers a compelling portrait of the transformative powers embedded in day-to-day existence. From soccer fields to dinner tables, the everyday emerges as a moral laboratory for reshaping moral life. Cheryl Mattingly offers vivid and heart-wrenching stories to elaborate a first-person ethical framework, forcefully showing the limits of third-person renderings of morality.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American familiesxCaliforniaxLos Angeles County. 0aAfrican American familieszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aChildren with disabilitiesxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectsxCaliforniaxLos Angeles County. 0aChildren with disabilitiesxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aChronically ill childrenxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectsxCaliforniaxLos Angeles County. 0aChronically ill childrenxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aMedical anthropologyxCaliforniaxLos Angeles County. 0aMedical anthropologyzCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aMedical ethicsxCaliforniaxLos Angeles County. 0aMedical ethicszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z978311062111240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095953840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959538423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959538/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles